'''Bureta Faraimo''' is a [[New Zealand]]-born [[rugby league]] player who represented the [[United States national rugby league team|United States]] in the [[2013 Rugby League World Cup|2013 World Cup]].
==Playing career==
A [[Wainuiomata Lions]] player, in 2010 Faraimo was selected to play for [[Wellington rugby league team|Wellington]] in the [[National Competition]] and also represented the [[New Zealand Residents]] side.<ref>[http://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/league/4121374/A-stroll-in-the-park-for-Faraimo-and-the-Orcas A stroll in the park for Faraimo and the Orcas] ''stuff.co.nz'', 13 August 2010</ref><ref>[http://www.nzrl.co.nz/nz-residents/nz-residents-2010.aspx NZ Residents 2010] ''nzrl.co.nz''</ref>

He then moved to Australia and played for the [[Mackay Cutters]] in the [[Queensland Cup]].<ref>[http://www.dailymercury.com.au/news/three-reasons-to-fear-faraimo/1872467/ Three reasons to fear Faraimo] ''dailymercury.com.au'', 18 May 2013</ref>

Qualifying because his dad was born on [[Swains Island]], Faraimo was named in the [[United States national rugby league team|United States]] squad for the [[2013 Rugby League World Cup|2013 World Cup]].<ref>[http://www.rlwc2013.com/rugby-league-world-news/article/1148/-man-squads-for-all-rlwc 24-man squads for all RLWC2013 nations announced] ''rlwc2013.com'', 9 October 2013</ref><ref>[http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/sport/nrl/mackay-cutters-winger-bureta-faraimo-on-cusp-of-realising-unlikely-nrl-dream/story-fni3fbgz-1226721339087 Mackay Cutters winger Bureta Faraimo on cusp of realising unlikely NRL dream] ''dailytelegraph.com.au'', 18 September 2013</ref>
